# C++ Standards

- C++20, no proprietary extensions
- Headers use `#pragma once`
- Qt: inherit `QObject`, use signals/slots for async
- HTTP callbacks via `std::function` in ZapClient
- No `using namespace std` in headers
- Prefer `const` and const references
- Domain errors: return via callback, no throw in hot paths
- **User-facing strings in English**

```cpp
// ✅ Centralized paths
const auto& cfg = AppConfig::instance();
m_client.setBaseUrl(cfg.zapApiUrl());

// ❌ Hardcode
m_baseUrl = "http://127.0.0.1:8080";
```
